    <h2 class="cag-h2">Is the African Grey the Best Talking Parrot?</h2>
    <a class="inf" href="/blog/african-grey-parrot-facts/"><img class="sec-img inf-img" src="/best-talking-parrot-ranking-grey-number-one.webp" srcset="/best-talking-parrot-ranking-grey-number-one-760.webp 760w, /best-talking-parrot-ranking-grey-number-one.webp 1376w" sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 760px" width="1376" height="768" alt="Best talking parrot ranking with the African Grey at number one ahead of Amazon and Eclectus" loading="lazy"></a>
    <p>Short answer: yes, and it is not especially close. The African Grey heads essentially every published best-talking-parrot list, and the reason is not raw word count but clarity and context — a Grey uses words in the right moment in a way no other companion parrot reliably does.</p>
