    <h3 class="cag-h3">Talking, Size and Noise at a Glance</h3>
    <p>The macaw is the showstopper — a metre of wingspan and a voice to fill a warehouse — but on talking clarity and apartment-livability the Grey wins comfortably. The trade is space and volume for cognition and quiet.</p>
    <h4 class="cag-h4">Who Each Bird Suits</h4>
    <p>A Grey suits a talking-focused owner in a normal-sized home; a macaw suits an owner with room, a tolerance for real volume, and a love of a big, bold, physical parrot.</p>
