    <h3 class="cag-h3">Independence, Noise and Dander at a Glance</h3>
    <p>Both are powder-down birds, so dust is a fact either way. The real split is temperament: a Grey is an independent worker happy to problem-solve alone, while a cockatoo is a velcro cuddler whose demand for contact — and whose scream — can overwhelm an unprepared home.</p>
    <h4 class="cag-h4">Who Each Bird Suits</h4>
    <p>Choose a Grey for talking and a workable noise level; choose a cockatoo only if you actively want a hands-on cuddle bird and can meet its intensity. Our African Grey vs Cockatoo breakdown weighs the cuddle-versus-talk trade in full.</p>
