    <h3 class="cag-h3">Talking vs Singing, Temperament and Dust</h3>
    <p>The Amazon is the extrovert of the pair — a confident singer and performer with loud, seasonal outbursts — while the Grey is the quieter thinker whose speech carries context. The Amazon produces less powder-down, but its hormonal seasons ask more of an owner's patience.</p>
    <h4 class="cag-h4">Who Each Bird Suits</h4>
    <p>Choose a Grey for contextual talking and a steadier temperament; choose an Amazon for an outgoing, musical bird in a household ready for its seasonal drama. The African Grey vs Amazon comparison covers the talking-versus-singing split in depth.</p>
