    <h3 class="cag-h3">Size, Price and Talking Onset</h3>
    <p>These are two subspecies of one bird with the same intelligence. The Congo is larger with the iconic bright red tail and runs $1,700–$3,500; the Timneh is smaller, often a touch calmer, tends to start talking earlier, wears a maroon tail and horn-coloured beak, and runs $1,500–$1,600.</p>
    <h4 class="cag-h4">Which Grey Fits Your Home</h4>
    <p>For an apartment or a first grey, many owners lean Timneh for its calmer, quieter nature; for the classic look and presence, Congo.</p>
