    <h2 class="cag-h2">Male vs Female African Grey</h2>
    <a class="inf" href="/male-vs-female-african-grey-parrots-for-sale/"><img class="sec-img inf-img" src="/male-vs-female-african-grey-side-by-side-comparison-chart.webp" srcset="/male-vs-female-african-grey-side-by-side-comparison-chart-760.webp 760w, /male-vs-female-african-grey-side-by-side-comparison-chart.webp 1376w" sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 760px" width="1376" height="768" alt="Male vs female African Grey comparison showing identical monomorphic appearance and DNA sexing" loading="lazy"></a>
    <p>Should you get a male or a female African Grey parrot? Buyers ask us this every week, and the honest answer surprises most of them — you cannot tell the sexes apart by eye, personality does not follow sex, and it is why we PCR DNA-sex every chick we place.</p>
    <div class="vs-metrics">
      <div class="vs-m"><span>Looks</span><b>Identical</b></div>
      <div class="vs-m"><span>Behaviour</span><b>Individual</b></div>
      <div class="vs-m"><span>Sexing</span><b>DNA only</b></div>
    </div>
    <h3 class="cag-h3">Appearance, Behaviour and DNA Sexing</h3>
    <p>African Greys are monomorphic — males and females look alike and behave alike as pets. Personality is individual, not sex-linked, and the only reliable way to know a Grey's sex is a PCR DNA test, which is why every bird we place is DNA-sexed.</p>
    <h4 class="cag-h4">Does Sex Actually Matter for a Pet Grey?</h4>
    <p>For a companion bird, almost never. Choose the individual whose temperament fits your home rather than a sex, and let the DNA certificate settle the paperwork.</p>
    <h5 class="cag-h5">Read the full male vs female guide</h5>
    <p>Our male-vs-female guide explains why you cannot eye-sex a Grey, what DNA-sexing proves, and when sex genuinely matters — for breeding, not for a pet.</p>
    <h6 class="cag-h6">At a glance: the gender takeaway</h6>
    <p>Pick the bird, not the sex — they are identical in looks and temperament, and DNA is the only certainty.</p>
  </section>

