    <p>Every African Grey we place is a trade: the clearest-talking, most intelligent companion parrot in aviculture, in exchange for real daily demands and a commitment measured in decades. Here is that ledger at its shortest.</p>
    <h3 class="cag-h3">The Honest Trade-Off in Three Lines</h3>
    <p>On the pro side: unmatched talking, child-level intelligence, and a bond that can last decades. On the con side: a 40–60 year commitment, hours of daily attention, powder-down dander, and a bird that plucks or bites when its needs go unmet. Our honest African Grey pros and cons guide weighs both columns in full, with a self-assessment to tell if a Grey actually fits your home.</p>
