    <a class="inf" href="/african-grey-parrot-lifespan/"><img class="sec-img inf-img" src="/african-grey-40-60-year-lifespan-timeline.webp" srcset="/african-grey-40-60-year-lifespan-timeline-760.webp 760w, /african-grey-40-60-year-lifespan-timeline.webp 1376w" sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 760px" width="1376" height="768" alt="African Grey lifespan timeline from weaning to sixty years with life-stage milestones" loading="lazy"></a>
    <p>A healthy African Grey routinely lives forty to sixty years — long enough to outlast careers, homes and sometimes owners. Before any comparison crowns a winner, this is the commitment every one of these parrots asks for.</p>
    <h3 class="cag-h3">Planning Honestly for a Lifetime Bird</h3>
    <p>Every parrot compared here is a long-lived bird, and the Grey is squarely a lifetime commitment — a healthy Grey commonly reaches 40 to 60 years, sometimes beyond. That single line reshapes the decision: it means naming a caretaker, budgeting for decades, and treating the choice as a multi-decade relationship rather than a purchase. Our African Grey lifespan guide covers the succession planning most buyers never think to do.</p>
